# sha256 hex digest

R.3.2 wires `sha256(s)` → `crate::runtime::_sha256` using the
`sha2 = "0.10"` crate (pulled into `Cargo.toml` only when the
program reaches `sha256`).

```scalascript
@main def run(): Unit =
  println(sha256("hello"))
```

Build and run:

```bash
ssc build-rust crypto-sha256.ssc
./crypto-sha256
# → 2cf24dba5fb0a30e26e83b2ac5b9e29e1b161e5c1fa7425e73043362938b9824
```

This matches `printf 'hello' | openssl dgst -sha256`.
